-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Scope
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"The Work" means this repository and its contents: the blueprint, registry,
governance doctrine, templates, skills, evaluations, scripts, schemas, and source
register.

The Work is proprietary and confidential to BPI Danantara and is made available
only to named individuals and entities who have been granted access in writing.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Permitted use
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Subject to a written authorization from the accountable Danantara owner, an
authorized recipient may use, reproduce, and modify the Work solely for the
internal purposes of BPI Danantara, DAM, DIM, DDMF, portfolio entities, and
authorized partners.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Restrictions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Except as expressly authorized in writing, no person may:

  - disclose, publish, distribute, or sublicense the Work to any third party
  - use the Work outside the entity, purpose, jurisdiction, and data
    classification for which access was granted
  - process the Work using models, tools, connectors, or environments that have
    not been approved for its classification

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. No authorization to decide
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Work describes AI-assisted analysis. It confers no mandate, no decision
right, and no approval authority. Nothing in the Work authorizes any person or
system to make, imply, or record an institutional decision on behalf of BPI
Danantara, DAM, DIM, or DDMF. Every material output remains a draft until the
competent human authority has approved it through the applicable governance
process.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. No warranty
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Work is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. It is build-ready,
not production-authorized. It has not been mapped to actual Danantara laws,
policies, delegations, committee charters, data classifications, or named human
owners, and it must not be deployed as though it has been.
